'''莱索托君主'''系指现今的[[莱索托王国|莱索托王国]]之[[国王|国王]]，在历史上巴苏托兰时期其尊号也曾称为“{{link-en|最高酋长|Paramount chief}}”({{lang-en|Paramount chief}})。同时本表也收录了其他以[[政变|政变]]、[[摄政|摄政]]，或[[代理|代理]]等方式暂时担任[[国家元首|国家元首]]的人物。现任莱索托王国之国王是1996年2月7日第二次加冕的[[莱齐耶三世|莱齐耶三世]]。

== 宪法地位 ==

依照1993年3月颁布的[[莱索托|莱索托]][[宪法|宪法]]规定:[[莱索托王国|莱索托王国]]为[[君主立宪制|君主立宪制]]国家，[[国王|国王]]是[[国家元首|国家元首]]，是民族团结与国家稳定的象征<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ls.mofcom.gov.cn/article/ddfg/tzzhch/200810/20081005834423.shtml|title=对外投资合作国别指南-------莱索托|accessdate=2014-07-07|author=郝永江|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=2008-10-16|year=|month=|format=|work=中华人民共和国驻莱索托王国大使馆经济商务参赞处|publisher=[[中华人民共和国商务部|中华人民共和国商务部]]|pages=1.3.1|language=zh-cn|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707051928/http://ls.mofcom.gov.cn/article/ddfg/tzzhch/200810/20081005834423.shtml|archivedate=2014-07-07|quote=莱索托政治体制为君主立宪制，按照1993年3月颁布生效的现行宪法规定，国王为国家元首和立宪君主|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。而[[行政权|行政权]]及[[立法权|立法权]]分别是由[[首相|首相]]与[[议会|议会]]来掌握，国王为[[虚位元首|虚位元首]]<ref name="About">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-13728326|title=Lesotho profile|accessdate=2014-07-07|author=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=13 March 2014|year=|month=|format=|work=[[BBC新闻|BBC新闻]]|publisher=|pages=|language=en|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140311050724/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-13728326|archivedate=2014-03-11|quote=The monarch has no legislative or executive powers.|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。其职权为根据议会之结果或首相之建议，以自身名义发布法律以及命令；出访外国或接待来访外国政治人物。

== 继承顺序 ==

莱索托是一个[[世袭|王位世袭]]的[[君主立宪制|君主立宪制]]国家，'''莱索托国王王位继承顺序'''依据1993年颁布实施之《{{link-fr|莱索托王国宪法|Constitution du Lesotho}}》第五章第四十五款之条文而确定<ref name="Constitution">{{harvnb|《Constitution of Lesotho》|1993|loc=Chapter V：Article 45：Section 1-2}}{{quote|'''''(1)''' The College of Chiefs may at any time designate, in accordance with the customary law of Lesotho,the person (or the persons, in order of prior right) who are entitled to succeed to the office of King upon the death of the holder of, or the occurrence of any vacancy in, that office and if on such death or vacancy, there is a person who has previously been designated in pursuance of this section and who is capable under the customary law of Lesotho of succeeding to that office, that person (or, if there is more than one such person, that one of them who has been designated as having the first right to succeed to the office) shall become King.'''(2)''' If, on the death of the holder of, or the occurrence of any vacancy in, the office of King, there is no person who becomes King under subsection (1), the College of Chiefs shall, with all practical speed and in accordance with the customary law of Lesotho, proceed to designate a person to succeed to the office of King and the person so designated shall thereupon become King.''}}</ref>。条文规定了王位继承人是由莱索托酋长院({{lang-en|Lesotho's College of Chiefs}})经商议后指定的<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.ls/king/|title=The Office of the King|accessdate=2015-01-25|author=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=|year=2010|month=|format=|work=|publisher='''''Parliament of the Kingdom of Lesotho[莱索托王国议会]'''''|pages=|language=en|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140805135949/http://www.parliament.ls/king/|archivedate=2014-08-05|quote=The King is designated by the College of Chiefs, in accordance with the customary law of Lesotho, upon the death of his predecessor or occurrence of a vacancy in the Office of King.|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。继承人可以是一位，抑或是按照次序排好的多位<ref name="Constitution"></ref>。而当国王逝世或退位，或者王位因故发生空缺时，王位继承人即可[[即位|继承王位]]<ref name="Constitution"></ref>。但当王位继承人在需要继承王位时仍未满二十一周岁；酋长院应指定一位[[摄政|摄政王]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.ls/king/|title=The Monarchy|accessdate=2015-01-25|author=|last=|first=|authorlink=|coauthors=|date=|year=2010|month=|format=|work=|publisher='''''Parliament of the Kingdom of Lesotho[莱索托王国议会]'''''|pages=|language=en|doi=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140805135949/http://www.parliament.ls/king/|archivedate=2014-08-05|quote=When the rightful heir to the throne has not yet attained the age of twenty-one, or the King is absent from Lesotho or is not in good health, there is provision for the appointment of a Regent.|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

而若现任国王正处于短期的病痛中，或是因故暂时性地出国期间；酋长院应按照莱索托的习惯法暂时指定专人代理行使国王之职能<ref name="Constitution1">{{harvnb|《Constitution of Lesotho》|1993|loc=Chapter V：Article 45：Section 3}}{{quote|'''''(3)''' Whenever the holder of the office of King or a Regent - '''(a)''' has occasion to be absent from Lesotho for a period which the College of Chiefs has reason to believe will be of short duration; or '''(b)''' is suffering from an illness which the College of Chiefs has reason to believe will be of short duration,the College of Chiefs may for the time being designate a person, in accordance with the customary law of Lesotho, to exercise the functions of the office of King, and any person for the time being so designated may exercise all the functions of the office of King during the absence or illness of the holder of that office or the Regent.''}}</ref>。

所有关于王位继承人、摄政王，及国王代理人的任命或变更，都必须公布在[[公文|政府公报]]之中<ref name="Constitution2">{{harvnb|《Constitution of Lesotho》|1993|loc=Chapter V：Article 45：Section 4}}{{quote|'''''(4)''' Every designation made for the purposes of this section shall be published in the Gazette.''}}</ref>。
